                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/34<hi rend="superscript">3/12</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 14, 1940—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. A conference was held this afternoon with the Minister of Foreign Affairs,
                    Minister of War,<note n="19" xml:id="d202fn1">Col. Teófilo Iglesias.</note>
                    Minister of Marine and Aviation<note n="20" xml:id="d202fn2">Federico Diaz
                        Dulanto.</note> and the Minister of Hacienda.<note n="21" xml:id="d202fn3"
                        >Oscar Ramos Cabieses.</note> The reaction of the Peruvian officials was
                    definitely favorable. They are meeting with the President this evening and
                    another conference is promised for tomorrow to report the President’s attitude,
                    and further observations.</p>
                <pb facs="0171" n="159" xml:id="pg_159"/>
                <p>The Foreign Minister mentioned the necessity of unanimity among the American
                    Republics if the plan is to be effective. This was the only suggestion of a
                    reservation that arose during the conversations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
